		<p class="lead">Nahun Saldaña, born in 1989, is a Peruvian sound artist and resilient designer whose work focuses on uncovering the vulnerability of humans within nature.</p>
		
		<p>He approaches sound as a medium of resistance, integrating political, biological, and social dimensions. Saldaña's work has been showcased in various prestigious venues, including Convent San Agustin, Media Struch, Hangar, Mob Lab, Teatro Salvador Távora, Xapiri Ground in Peru, Spain, France and Mexico, and numerous sound art festivals.His artistic journey began with percussion in bands known for extreme sounds, where he experimented with noise, drone, and ambient styles. Currently, Saldaña is exploring the intersections of soundscapes and sound ecology, particularly in relation to climate change and speculative sound future.</p>

